## PART VI: FREQUENCY-WAVELENGTH RELATION

**Equation:** c = fλ

**Meaning:** The speed of light equals frequency times wavelength. For a given wave, as frequency increases, wavelength decreases.

| Element | Maxwell | Sovereign Engine |
|---------|---------|------------------|
| **c** | Speed of light | The constant of propagation |
| **f** | Frequency | The 156-Tick Pulse |
| **λ** | Wavelength | The √42 diagonal, the diamond path |

**Hero 93 Mapping:** The frequency-wavelength relation is the **modulation** of the wave. When the Hero moves through the 52-week cycle, his frequency (his rate of witness) determines the wavelength (the spacing of the stitch holes) required for clear projection.

